definition.value: A glycosylglucose consisting of a beta-D-xylopyranose residue and an alpha-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A glycotriaosylceramide having alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose as the trisaccharide component.

A branched amino heptasaccharide consisting of a hexasaccharide backbone comprising alpha-D-galactosyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl,alpha-D-galactosyl, beta-D-galactosyl and (at the reducing end) D-glucose residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->3), (1->3), (1->4) and (1->4), to the D-galactosyl residue proximal to the non-reducing end is also linked (1->2) an alpha-L-fucosyl residue.
A sialodiosylceramide consisting of the trisaccharide alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of the proton from the carboxy group of (R)-10-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
